91	95	\N	Capital Goods	{"pb_01": "information_available", "pb_02": "information_available", "pb_03": "information_available", "pb_04": "information_available", "pb_05": "Yes, there is a grievance mechanism in place for following stakeholders", "pb_06": "Information Available", "pb_07": "Information available", "pb_08": "information_available", "pb_09": "Information available", "pb_10": "information_available", "pb_11": "information_available", "pb_12": "information_available", "pb_13": "LCA conducted", "pb_14": "information_available", "pb_15": "information_available", "pb_16": "information_available", "pb_17": "information_available", "pb_18": "information_available", "pb_19": "information_available", "pb_20": "information_available", "pb_21": "information_available", "pb_22": "information_available", "pb_23": "information_available", "pb_24": "information_available", "pb_25": "information_available", "pb_26": "information_available", "pb_27": "information_available", "pb_28": "information_available", "pb_29": "information_available", "pb_30": "information_available", "pb_31": "information_available", "pb_32": "information_available", "pb_33": "information_available", "pb_34": "information_available", "pb_35": "information_available", "pb_01_textarea": "", "pb_02_textarea": "", "pb_03_textarea": "", "pb_04_textarea": "", "pb_05_textarea": "The Company’s Business Ethics Helpline is a channel for all its employees and stakeholders to report suspected violations of the ABB Code of Conduct, Supplier Code of\\nConduct, or applicable laws. Apart from this, the Customer Care Response Process (CCRP) is the process for the Company’s customers to raise any grievance with the Company’s\\nproduct, system and solution offering and service portfolio.\\nThe Company also has a dedicated email: investor.helpdesk@in.abb.com for addressing investor related queries.\\nAny complaints pertaining to sexual harassment can be raised by sending an email to: in-internal-committee-posh@abb.com", "pb_06_textarea": "ABB’s Code of Conduct applies globally to all of ABB’s employees,\\nmanagers, officers, directors, consultants, self-employed contractors,\\ncasual workers, agency workers and volunteers.", "pb_07_textarea": "https://global.abb/group/en/sustainability/social-progress/human-rights", "pb_08_textarea": "The Company has a CSR Committee of the Board which oversees the CSR performance in the year. It consists of four members including the Managing Director. Further, the Committee is chaired by a Woman Independent Director.\\n\\nFor composition of the CSR Committee, please refer Page No. 148 of the Annual Report in the Corporate Governance Section. Country Sustainability Boards have been established to uphold good sustainability governance and assure compliance with local legislations, ABB Group standards and customer expectations. The Sustainability Board at the country level is chaired by the Country Managing Director and includes the Country Finance Officer, Country Human Resources and Business Heads of Individual Businesses who anchor their\\nrespective Business Sustainability Boards. The Sustainability Boards discuss, review, and monitor on key sustainability performance indicators every quarter and decides on action plans, if any to achieve the same.", "pb_09_textarea": "", "pb_10_textarea": "The Company is committed to operating with the highest standards of ethics, business conduct, and professional behavior.\\n\\nThe Company has a Code of Conduct where anti-corruption and anti-bribery aspects are comprehensively covered. In line with the Code, the Company does not tolerate any form of bribery or corruption.", "pb_11_textarea": "", "pb_12_textarea": "", "pb_13_textarea": "", "pb_14_textarea": "", "pb_15_textarea": "ABB’s Equal Employment Opportunity (EEO) and Affirmative Action Employer encourages diversity in the workplace. All qualified applicants receive consideration for employment without regard to their sex, gender identity, sexual orientation, race, colour, religious, creed, national origin, physical or mental disability, protected veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by law. In line with Rights of Persons with Disabilities Act, 2016, differently-abled persons too receive equal treatment.\\n\\nWeblink: Equal Employment Opportunity and Affirmative Action\\n\\nThe Company rolled out and Equal Employment Opportunity Policy during the year. The policy set out “no discrimination” on the grounds of any ground including sex, mental status, race, caste, religion, color, ancestry, marital status, gender, sexual orientation, age, nationality ethnic origin, disability or any category. The Company’s employment decisions are solely based on legitimate job-related criteria and are made without discrimination.\\n\\nAny violation of the said policy can be reported through available reporting channels which includes raising it with\\nmanagement chain, or with any of the Company’s human resources or legal and integrity team and also can raise it in the Company’s available Business ethics helpline. Issues thus raised are inquired into in conjunction with relevant stakeholders and appropriate action is taken by the Company.", "pb_16_textarea": "", "pb_17_textarea": "", "pb_18_textarea": "All employees undergo career development reviews. With regards to the worker category,\\nthey are covered under the long-term settlement/ collective agreements with the unions.", "pb_19_textarea": "The ABB Way Health Safety Environment & Security (HSE&S) management system is consistent with ISO standards ISO 14001/ ISO 45001/ISO 50001. It aims to provide a common structure for the management of all HSE&S risks, setting minimum requirements to be followed unless local regulatory or legislative requirements impose a higher standard, in which case that higher standard shall be followed.\\n\\nThe management system is comprised of and detailed within ‘Management Standards’ and issue based ‘Control Standards’ together with supporting documentation as published in ABB’s Management Information System (MIS) document control module. The ABB Way defines how we manage HSE&S and sets clear expectations and the required minimum standards, which shall be implemented and embedded into all ABB operations and activities.\\n\\nYes\\n\\nYes", "pb_20_textarea": "", "pb_21_textarea": "", "pb_22_textarea": "", "pb_23_textarea": "Updated as per pdf. xml has wrong data", "pb_24_textarea": "", "pb_25_textarea": "As per pdf", "pb_26_textarea": "Yes, Human rights are part of the integrity clauses both sales and buy side.", "pb_27_textarea": "", "pb_28_textarea": "ISO audits are not acceptable as Independent assessment", "pb_29_textarea": "ISO audits are not acceptable as Independent assessment", "pb_30_textarea": "true", "pb_31_textarea": "true", "pb_32_textarea": "", "pb_33_textarea": "", "pb_34_textarea": "", "pb_35_textarea": "Please refer the link here with regard to cyber security: https://global.abb/group/en/technology/cyber-security and\\nplease refer the link here with regard to data privacy: https://new.abb.com/privacy", "pb_07_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_08_option_radio": "ESG/Sustainability function part of other board committee", "pb_10_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_13_percentage_1": "7.9", "pb_13_percentage_2": "7.2", "pb_15_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_19_option_radio": "Company has OHS management system, process to identify & process to report risks", "pb_26_option_radio": "Yes, it does", "pb_35_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_06_option1_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_06_option2_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_12_option_number": "100.0", "pb_33_option_number": "0", "pb_02_option_number1": "2", "pb_02_option_number2": "2", "pb_03_option_number1": "50.0", "pb_03_option_number2": "0.0", "pb_28_option_checkbox": "", "pb_29_option_checkbox": "", "pb_30_option_checkbox": "", "pb_31_option_checkbox": "", "