186	206	\N	Capital Goods	{"pb_01": "information_available", "pb_02": "information_available", "pb_03": "information_available", "pb_04": "information_available", "pb_05": "information_available", "pb_06": "Information Available", "pb_07": "Information available", "pb_08": "information_available", "pb_09": "Information available", "pb_10": "information_available", "pb_11": "information_available", "pb_12": "information_available", "pb_13": "No information", "pb_14": "information_available", "pb_15": "information_available", "pb_16": "information_available", "pb_17": "information_available", "pb_18": "information_available", "pb_19": "information_available", "pb_20": "information_available", "pb_21": "information_available", "pb_22": "information_available", "pb_23": "information_available", "pb_24": "information_available", "pb_25": "information_available", "pb_26": "information_available", "pb_27": "information_available", "pb_28": "information_available", "pb_29": "information_available", "pb_30": "information_available", "pb_31": "information_available", "pb_32": "information_available", "pb_33": "information_available", "pb_34": "information_available", "pb_35": "information_available", "pb_01_textarea": "", "pb_02_textarea": "", "pb_03_textarea": "", "pb_04_textarea": "", "pb_05_textarea": "https://apar.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/Whistle-Blower-Policy-APAR.pdf", "pb_06_textarea": "https://apar.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/APAR_Code_Of_Conduct_2022.pdf", "pb_07_textarea": "https://apar.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Social_Policies/13.Human_Rights_Policy.pdf", "pb_08_textarea": "Yes, the Board of APAR Industries has established Corporate Social Responsibility and Sustainability (CSR&S) Committee for overseeing and managing APAR's key sustainability-related issues, as detailed below:\\nCorporate Social Responsibility and Sustainability (CSR&S) Committee -- The CSR&S committee of the Board governs and reviews the Corporate Social Responsibility and Sustainability activities of the Company. The CSR&S Committee recommends the annual business plan for APAR’s CSR and Sustainability initiatives to the Board for its approval. The main responsibilities of the committee include reviewing sustainability goals, objectives, and strategies consistent with APAR’s mission, values, and long-term interests.; reviewing APAR’s ESG risks and opportunities and recommend actions to mitigate risks and capitalize on opportunities; reviewing targets for ESG performance and report to the Board; monitoring APAR’s performance against established sustainability metrics, targets, and benchmarks; reviewing sustainability-related policies, programs, and initiatives etc.", "pb_09_textarea": "", "pb_10_textarea": "https://apar.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Anti-Corruption-Anti-Bribery-Policy.pdf", "pb_11_textarea": "", "pb_12_textarea": "", "pb_13_textarea": "", "pb_14_textarea": "", "pb_15_textarea": "https://apar.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Social_Policies/8.Equal_Opportunity_Accessibility_Policy_for_Persons_with_\\nDisabilities.pdf", "pb_16_textarea": "", "pb_17_textarea": "", "pb_18_textarea": "", "pb_19_textarea": "Yes, we have implemented a robust health and safety management system across our business.\\nAll APAR’s manufacturing locations have been certified for OHSAS-18001/ ISO 45001 for Occupational Health & Safety; undertakes regular safety audits to identify hazardous acts; ensure compliance with standard operating procedures; and assess the performance of the company’s safety measures.\\n\\nThe certificates are uploaded at our website, and can be accessed through:\\nhttps://apar.com/apar-esg-report/ under the ‘Certificates’ tab.\\nIn addition to a collaborative approach for continual improvement and promotion of Health & Safety at the\\nworkplace, each plant has been equipped with:\\na) safety & 5S committee\\nb) suggestion scheme\\nc) Kaizen\\nd) Safety engagement activities, and\\ne) a team of qualified H&S professionals at each manufacturing location\\n\\nHazard Identification and Risk Assessment (\\"HIRA\\") is used for routine and non-routine activities. When there is a change in the workplace, such as to a production line layout, equipment, applicable legal requirements, we conduct hazard identification and risk assessments to prevent new hazards and reduce risks.  Each manufacturing location conducts hazard and risk assessments annually to determine if additional precautions are needed for health and safety management. We engage employees and encourage participation in health and safety management. This program enables employees to understand how to identify potential risks and hazards in their daily work environment. Through this and other programs, we are able to increase awareness and implement a sense of ownership in maintaining a safe workplace for everyone.\\n\\nYes\\n\\nYes", "pb_20_textarea": "", "pb_21_textarea": "", "pb_22_textarea": "", "pb_23_textarea": "", "pb_24_textarea": "", "pb_25_textarea": "", "pb_26_textarea": "", "pb_27_textarea": "", "pb_28_textarea": "true", "pb_29_textarea": "false", "pb_30_textarea": "true", "pb_31_textarea": "true", "pb_32_textarea": "", "pb_33_textarea": "", "pb_34_textarea": "", "pb_35_textarea": "https://apar.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/03_Data_Privacy_Policy-WS.pdf", "pb_07_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_08_option_radio": "Dedicated Board ESG/Sustainability committee", "pb_10_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_13_percentage_1": "", "pb_13_percentage_2": "", "pb_15_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_19_option_radio": "Company has OHS management system, process to identify & process to report risks", "pb_26_option_radio": "Yes, it does", "pb_35_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_06_option1_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_06_option2_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_12_option_number": "59.1", "pb_33_option_number": "", "pb_02_option_number1": "4", "pb_02_option_number2": "4