104	110	\N	Capital Goods	{"pb_01": "information_available", "pb_02": "information_available", "pb_03": "information_available", "pb_04": "information_available", "pb_05": "information_available", "pb_06": "Information Available", "pb_07": "Information available", "pb_08": "information_available", "pb_09": "No clear information", "pb_10": "information_available", "pb_11": "No information", "pb_12": "No clear information", "pb_13": "LCA conducted", "pb_14": "No clear information", "pb_15": "information_available", "pb_16": "information_available", "pb_17": "information_available", "pb_18": "information_available", "pb_19": "information_available", "pb_20": "information_available", "pb_21": "information_available", "pb_22": "information_available", "pb_23": "information_available", "pb_24": "No information", "pb_25": "information_available", "pb_26": "information_available", "pb_27": "information_available", "pb_28": "information_available", "pb_29": "information_available", "pb_30": "information_available", "pb_31": "information_available", "pb_32": "information_available", "pb_33": "No clear information", "pb_34": "information_available", "pb_35": "information_available", "pb_01_textarea": "The company does not have other than permanent employees", "pb_02_textarea": "", "pb_03_textarea": "", "pb_04_textarea": "company has no female permanent workers. Hence, removed 0", "pb_05_textarea": "", "pb_06_textarea": "https://everestkanto.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/EKCL-Code-of-Conduct-and-Ethics-for-Baord-and-Senior-Management.pdf\\n\\"The Company also has laid down an Ethics policy to ensure ethical conduct by employees, supply chain &business partners.\\n\\" However, the policy was not available on the website.", "pb_07_textarea": "Company states to have a policy in place, but the same was not found in public domain.", "pb_08_textarea": "Mr. Puneet Khurana, Managing Director, oversees the Business Responsibility and Sustainability\\ninitiatives of the Company.", "pb_09_textarea": "", "pb_10_textarea": "The company has a Code of Conduct for Directors and Senior Management that entails ethical conduct. The Company also has laid down an Ethics policy to ensure ethical conduct by employees, supply chain & business partners. But the policy is not available on website.", "pb_11_textarea": "Capital\\nexpenditure and R&D spends incurred by the Company embeds cost incurred to mitigate environmental & social hazards. These are\\ninseparable cost of the projects and hence separately identifying such cost is not feasible. Increasing share of renewable energy in\\noverall energy portfolio is a flagship initiative which demonstrated our commitment towards sourcing clean energy and transition to\\nlow carbon operation having a direct impact on the environment.", "pb_12_textarea": "", "pb_13_textarea": "", "pb_14_textarea": "", "pb_15_textarea": "We strongly believe in respecting the individuality of our employees and are committed to creating a healthy, safe, and secure work environment that enables employees to work without fear of prejudice, gender bias, and sexual harassment. We ensure that no employee is at a disadvantage based on disability and we aim to provide equal opportunities for all the employees.", "pb_16_textarea": "Company has no women permanent workers.", "pb_17_textarea": "No women workers", "pb_18_textarea": "No women workers", "pb_19_textarea": "The Company has complete focus on health and well-being of its employees. Awareness sessions are conducted on safety related aspects for the employees. Training related to Hazard Analysis Critical Control Point (HACCP) and Total Productive Maintenance are also provided. The Company is focused on both, the physical and mental well-being of its employees and has organized various programs and discussions with well-being experts and medical practitioners. Occupational Health and Safety management system has been implemented at EKC. The system covers all employees, workers, operational locations and townships. Operational / Product Safety related trainings and stakeholder engagement exercises are undertaken with local communities and customers as well. The management system is reviewed internally every year, and it is also externally certified at operating units. The efficacy of the management system is maintained and improved as part of the company-wide risk management and control process, and it is aligned with our safety principle.\\n\\nWe have implemented the process to identify the work-related Hazard Identification and Risk Assessment (HIRA) on a daily routine basis. The work-related hazards are also identified and evaluated as per procedure for Identification and Evaluation of Environmental Aspect and Occupational Health & Safety hazards and records of the same are updated in the Aspect and hazard evaluation register. We also identify workplace hazards through:\\n• Daily Safety Inspection by plant team, safety personnel and night duty officers;\\n• Weekly safety inspection by senior officials;\\n• Daily safety toolbox talk;\\n• Weekly shop floor safety meeting with workmen;\\n• Routine identification of unsafe conditions and unsafe acts;\\n• Capturing and reporting of near miss incident from shop floor personnel;\\n• Work permits by plant and safety personnel;\\n• Through Safety Observation Tour (SOT) at plant.\\n\\nYes\\n\\nYes", "pb_20_textarea": "", "pb_21_textarea": "", "pb_22_textarea": "", "pb_23_textarea": "No women workers", "pb_24_textarea": "", "pb_25_textarea": "", "pb_26_textarea": "Yes", "pb_27_textarea": "", "pb_28_textarea": "Converted to per crore rupee of turnover", "pb_29_textarea": "Converted to per crore rupee of turnover", "pb_30_textarea": "false", "pb_31_textarea": "", "pb_32_textarea": "", "pb_33_textarea": "No, the Company does not have any preferential procurement policy focusing on suppliers from marginalised / vulnerable groups", "pb_34_textarea": "", "pb_35_textarea": "https://everestkanto.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/12/Data-Privacy-Policy.pdf", "pb_07_option_radio": "Internal Policy", "pb_08_option_radio": "No dedicated board committee, but MD/CEO/CFO/COO or any other executive with multiple responsibilities is also responsible for sustainability issues", "pb_10_option_radio": "Internal Policy", "pb_13_percentage_1": "", "pb_13_percentage_2": "96", "pb_15_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_19_option_radio": "Company has OHS management system, process to identify & process to report risks", "pb_26_option_radio": "Yes, it does", "pb_35_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_06_option1_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_06_option2_radio": "Internal Policy", "pb_12_option_number": "", "pb_33_option_number": "0.0", "pb_02_option_number1": "1", "pb_02_option_number2": "0", "pb_03_option_number1": "33.34", "pb_03_option_number2": "0.0", "pb_28_option_checkbox": "", "pb_29_option_checkbox": "", "pb_30_option_checkbox": "", "pb_31_option_checkbox": "", "pb_05_option_checkbox1": "Employees", "pb_05_option_checkbox2": "Workers", "pb_05_option_checkbox3": "Communities", "pb_05_option_checkbox4": "Value chain partners", "pb_05_option_checkbox5": "Customers", "pb_13_option_checkbox2": "", "pb_24_option1_checkbox": "", "pb_06_option1_checkbox1": "Code of conduct for Board of Directors/KMPs", "pb_06_option2_checkbox2": "Code of conduct for employees", "pb_14_option1_checkbox1": "", "pb_20_option1_checkbox1": "Lost Time Injury Frequency Rate", "pb_20_option1_checkbox2": "Fatalities", "pb_01_table_row1_number1": "97.62", "pb_01_table_row1_number2": "2.39", "pb_01_table_row1_number3": "100.0", "pb_01_table_row1_number4": "0.0", "pb_01_table_row2_number1": "", "pb_01_table_row2_number2": "", "pb_01_table_row2_number3": "100.0", "pb_01_table_row2_number4": "0.0", "pb_01_table_row3_number1": "97.62", "pb_01_table_row3_number2": "2.39", "pb_01_table_row3_number3": "100.0", "pb_01_table_row3_number4": "0.0", "pb_04_table_row1_number1": "3.62", "pb_04_table_row1_number2"