152	159	\N	FMCG	{"pb_01": "information_available", "pb_02": "information_available", "pb_03": "information_available", "pb_04": "information_available", "pb_05": "information_available", "pb_06": "Information Available", "pb_07": "Information available", "pb_08": "information_available", "pb_09": "No clear information", "pb_10": "information_available", "pb_11": "information_available", "pb_12": "information_available", "pb_13": "No LCA conducted", "pb_14": "information_available", "pb_15": "information_available", "pb_16": "information_available", "pb_17": "information_available", "pb_18": "information_available", "pb_19": "information_available", "pb_20": "information_available", "pb_21": "information_available", "pb_22": "information_available", "pb_23": "information_available", "pb_24": "information_available", "pb_25": "information_available", "pb_26": "information_available", "pb_27": "information_available", "pb_28": "information_available", "pb_29": "information_available", "pb_30": "information_available", "pb_31": "No information", "pb_32": "information_available", "pb_33": "information_available", "pb_34": "information_available", "pb_35": "information_available", "pb_01_textarea": "", "pb_02_textarea": "", "pb_03_textarea": "", "pb_04_textarea": "", "pb_05_textarea": "The Company through its Registrar and Transfer Agent (RTA), provides redressal to shareholder grievances. The Company has specific e-mail addresses earmarked for receiving shareholder complaints, viz rnt.helpdesk@linkintime.co.in and isc@godfreyphillips.co.in. The web link for Whistleblower Policy is: https://www.godfreyphillips.co.in/public/storage/images/policies/Whistle%20Blower%20-%20English.pdf", "pb_06_textarea": "Link to policy - https://www.godfreyphillips.co.in/public/storage/images/policies/Code%20of%20Business%20Conduct.pdf ", "pb_07_textarea": "https://www.godfreyphillips.co.in/public/storage/images/policies/Human%20Rights%20Policy.pdf", "pb_08_textarea": "Yes, the Company has a Board level ESG Committee which enables the integration of ESG into businesses by providing inputs for envisioning the journey and targets. The Committee will also review ESG investments for long term purposes to steer and provide impetus to the organization into a sustainable future. The composition of the Committee is as follows:\\n1. Mr. Sharad Aggarwal- Whole-Time Director, Functional Chief Executive Officer\\n2. Dr. Lalit Bhasin- Non-Executive, Independent\\n3. Mr. Atul Kumar Gupta- Non-Executive, Independent\\n4. Mr. Subramanian Lakshminarayanan- Non-Executive, Independent", "pb_09_textarea": "", "pb_10_textarea": "GPIL prioritizes ethical conduct with a strong Anti-Corruption & Anti-Bribery Policy aligned with relevant laws. This zero-tolerance policy applies to employees, directors, and suppliers, with a Supplier Code of Conduct reinforcing these expectations. An Ethics Committee ensures effective policy implementation. The policy can be viewed at https://www.godfreyphillips.co.in/public/storage/images/policies/Anti-Bribery%20and%20Anti-Corruption%20(ABAC)%20Policy.pdf", "pb_11_textarea": "", "pb_12_textarea": "", "pb_13_textarea": "GPIL recognises a Lifecycle Assessment (LCA) is crucial for environmental impact measurement. However, GPIL hasn't conducted a comprehensive LCA yet. This limits their understanding of the full environmental impact. Despite this, GPIL remains committed to sustainability and has implemented initiatives to optimise the use of energy, water, and reduction of waste. ", "pb_14_textarea": "", "pb_15_textarea": "https://godfreyphillips.co.in/public/storage/images/policies/Equal%20Opportunity%20Policy.pdf", "pb_16_textarea": "", "pb_17_textarea": "", "pb_18_textarea": "", "pb_19_textarea": "Yes. GPIL has a management system for occupational health and safety that is accredited to ISO 45001:2018. The system is thoroughly documented and used throughout GPIL’s factory operations. The system is effectively supported by several committees, which promote safety activities to go along with the objective of compliance with occupational health and safety measures. Certified external auditors conduct audits of this system annually. For corporate office and branches, we have a process and an internal assessment method for health and safety. For manufacturing facilities and offices, the Company also periodically organizes health screenings, vaccination drives, and sessions on fitness and wellbeing, and maintain a safe and hygienic work environment.  GPIL takes a proactive approach to safety with a comprehensive EHS Risk Management framework especially for their manufacturing and operation units. This framework includes a set of processes for continual risk\\nidentification, assessment, and mitigation, with active participation of the workforce in each of its facilities. Shop floor processes in this regard include hazard spotting tours, suggestion schemes, daily briefings, and periodic EHS committee meetings in which employees participate. Furthermore, GPIL has a Hazard Identification and Risk Assessment (HIRA) and regularly conducts Job Safety Analysis for individual tasks. A process for ISO, ASPECT IMPACT, OCP and Training and Awareness programs are present to cater to work related hazards. To address near-miss incidents, the Company has created control measures that are intended to reduce the identified workplace hazards and record them in the risk register.", "pb_20_textarea": "", "pb_21_textarea": "", "pb_22_textarea": "", "pb_23_textarea": "", "pb_24_textarea": "", "pb_25_textarea": "", "pb_26_textarea": "Yes", "pb_27_textarea": "", "pb_28_textarea": "", "pb_29_textarea": "", "pb_30_textarea": "", "pb_31_textarea": "", "pb_32_textarea": "", "pb_33_textarea": "", "pb_34_textarea": "", "pb_35_textarea": "https://www.godfreyphillips.co.in/public/storage/images/policies/InformationSecurityPolicy.pdf", "pb_07_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_08_option_radio": "No dedicated board committee, but MD/CEO/CFO/COO or any other executive with multiple responsibilities is also responsible for sustainability issues", "pb_10_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_13_percentage_1": "", "pb_13_percentage_2": "", "pb_15_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_19_option_radio": "Company has OHS management system, process to identify & process to report risks", "pb_26_option_radio": "Yes, it does", "pb_35_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_06_option1_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_06_option2_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_12_option_number": "25.0", "pb_33_option_number": "5.0", "pb_02_option_number1": "1", "pb_02_option_number2": "0", "pb_03_option_number1": "22.23", "pb_03_option_number2": "20.0", "pb_28_option_checkbox": "", "pb_29_option_checkbox": "", "pb_30_option_checkbox": "", "pb_31_option_checkbox": "", "pb_05_option_checkbox1": "Employees", "pb_05_option_checkbox2": "Workers", "pb_05_option_checkbox3": "Communities", "pb_05_option_checkbox4": "Value chain partners", "pb_05_option_checkbox5": "Customers", "pb_13_option_checkbox2": "", "pb_24_option1_checkbox": "", "pb_06_option1_checkbox1": "Code of conduct for Board of Directors/KMPs", "pb_06_option2_checkbox2": "Code of conduct for employees", "pb_14_option1_checkbox1": "", "pb_20_option1_checkbox1": "Lost Time Injury Frequency Rate", "pb_20_option1_checkbox2": "Fatalities", "pb_01_table_row1_number1": "93.84", "pb_01_table_row1_number2": "6.17", "pb_01_table_row1_number3": "100.0", "pb_01_table_row1_number4": "0.0", "pb_01_table_row2_number1": "", "pb_01_table_row2_number2": "", "pb_01_table_row2_number3": "", "pb_01_table_row2_number4": "", "pb_01_table_row3_number1": "93.84", "pb_01_table_row3_number2": "6.17", "pb_01_table_row3_number3": "100.0", "pb_01_table_row3_number4": "0.0", "pb_04_table_row1_number1": "14.0", "pb_04_table_row1_number2": "12.5", "pb_04_table_row1_number3": "11.9", "pb_04_table_row2_number1": "6.5", "pb_04_table_row2_number2": "7.0", 