er corruption in every country in which we do business. This is covered in our Whistle Blowing Policy and the same is available on our website.\\n\\nhttps://www.asterdmhealthcare.in/fileadmin/user_upload/TheAsterianEthosOurCodeofConduct_01.pdf, pg 14", "pb_11_textarea": "", "pb_12_textarea": "No. Since, the Company is in healthcare business, the products have to be sourced as per regulatory and patient safety requirements.\\nHence, this is not applicable to the Company", "pb_13_textarea": "This activity hasn’t been carried out for the financial year.", "pb_14_textarea": "", "pb_15_textarea": "https://www.asterdmhealthcare.in/fileadmin/user_upload/TheAsterianEthosOurCodeofConduct_01.pdf, pg 11", "pb_16_textarea": "There are no workers in the company", "pb_17_textarea": "There are no workers in the company", "pb_18_textarea": "There are no workers in the company", "pb_19_textarea": "Occupational Safety and Health Administration (‘OSHA’) guidelines are followed in all the units. There is an annual risk assessment done in all areas of the hospital, location wise and possible risks/hazards are identified and scored. Based on the scores, mitigation strategies are also implemented to ensure risk is low. There is a mandatory training given to all staff in OSHA as part of induction training and annual refresher trainings by HR & Safety Officer. This also includes mock drills in concerned risk areas. Records are maintained for the training and mock drills by the unit HR & Safety Officer. We also have an incident reporting system which permits staff and supervisors to report occurrence of such events. Root cause analysis and CAPA are done and required actions are put in place for preventing reoccurrence. Key metrics such as needle stick injuries, blood and body fluid exposure, staff immunization compliance, hand hygiene compliance, etc., are monitored on a regular basis and presented to the management. Pre exposure prophylaxis in terms of vaccination for all healthcare workers and staff handling bio medical waste (Hep B) is a mandate. This is checked as a part of joining formalities and vaccination is given prior to joining as applicable (not received or low HbSAg titre). The compliance to the same is checked and monitored on a regular basis by the Infection control team and is also a KPI monitored in the Infection control dashboard.\\n\\nThere is an exercise for Hazard Identification & Risk Assessment done annually in all the units which is location wise. Along with this, all staff are encouraged to report incidents related to work site injuries. Facility rounds by a multi-disciplinary team are a must once every month and the findings are presented in the monthly held safety committee meetings. Most of the issues are resolved real time, however, the pending ones and the report of the facility rounds is presented in the safety committee. There is a safety program for the hospital which is reviewed every quarter in the safety committee and revised on an annual basis. This includes occupational safety, lab, radiology, patient, clinical, facility and infection control safety. Monthly surveillance is conducted by the Infection control team and the safety team. Infection control risk assessment, Pre-construction risk assessment (prior to construction or renovation inside the hospital) are done regularly, Audiometry tests are done annually for staff working in high noise areas.\\n\\nYes\\n\\nYes", "pb_20_textarea": "", "pb_21_textarea": "", "pb_22_textarea": "There are no workers in the company", "pb_23_textarea": "There are no workers in the company", "pb_24_textarea": "", "pb_25_textarea": "", "pb_26_textarea": "Yes, by inclusion of Anti Child Labor & Anti Trafficking clauses in business agreements and contracts.", "pb_27_textarea": "", "pb_28_textarea": "Converted intensity for per crore INr of revenue", "pb_29_textarea": "Converted intensity for per crore INr of revenue", "pb_30_textarea": "Converted intensity for per crore INr of revenue", "pb_31_textarea": "", "pb_32_textarea": "", "pb_33_textarea": "No, the company adheres strictly to a procurement policy where quality compliance is the sole parameter in healthcare setup.", "pb_34_textarea": "", "pb_35_textarea": "https://www.asterdmhealthcare.in/fileadmin/user_upload/Risk_Management_Policy.pdf", "pb_07_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_08_option_radio": "ESG/Sustainability function part of other board committee", "pb_10_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_13_percentage_1": "", "pb_13_percentage_2": "", "pb_15_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_19_option_radio": "Company has OHS management system, process to identify & process to report risks", "pb_26_option_radio": "Yes, it does", "pb_35_option_radio": "Internal Policy", "pb_06_option1_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_06_option2_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_12_option_number": "", "pb_33_option_number": "0", "pb_02_option_number1": "41", "pb_02_option_number2": "", "pb_03_option_number1": "20.0", "pb_03_option_number2": "20.0", "pb_28_option_checkbox": "", "pb_29_option_checkbox": "", "pb_30_option_checkbox": "", "pb_31_option_checkbox": "", "pb_05_option_checkbox1": "Employees", "pb_05_option_checkbox2": "", "pb_05_option_checkbox3": "Communities", "pb_05_option_checkbox4": "Value chain partners", "pb_05_option_checkbox5": "Customers", "pb_13_option_checkbox2": "", "pb_24_option1_checkbox": "", "pb_06_option1_checkbox1": "Code of conduct for Board of Directors/KMPs", "pb_06_option2_checkbox2": "Code of conduct for employees", "pb_14_option1_checkbox1": "", "pb_20_option1_checkbox1": "Lost Time Injury Frequency Rate", "pb_20_option1_checkbox2": "Fatalities", "pb_01_table_row1_number1": "33.86", "pb_01_table_row1_number2": "66.15", "pb_01_table_row1_number3": "", "pb_01_table_row1_number4": "", "pb_01_table_row2_number1": "52.63", "pb_01_table_row2_number2": "47.38", "pb_01_table_row2_number3": "", "pb_01_table_row2_number4": "", "pb_01_tab