98	104	\N	Oil, Gas & Consumablefuels	{"pb_01": "information_available", "pb_02": "information_available", "pb_03": "information_available", "pb_04": "information_available", "pb_05": "Yes, there is a grievance mechanism in place for following stakeholders", "pb_06": "Information Available", "pb_07": "Information available", "pb_08": "information_available", "pb_09": "No clear information", "pb_10": "information_available", "pb_11": "information_available", "pb_12": "information_available", "pb_13": "LCA conducted", "pb_14": "information_available", "pb_15": "information_available", "pb_16": "information_available", "pb_17": "information_available", "pb_18": "information_available", "pb_19": "information_available", "pb_20": "information_available", "pb_21": "information_available", "pb_22": "information_available", "pb_23": "information_available", "pb_24": "information_available", "pb_25": "information_available", "pb_26": "information_available", "pb_27": "information_available", "pb_28": "information_available", "pb_29": "information_available", "pb_30": "information_available", "pb_31": "information_available", "pb_32": "information_available", "pb_33": "information_available", "pb_34": "information_available", "pb_35": "information_available", "pb_01_textarea": "", "pb_02_textarea": "", "pb_03_textarea": "", "pb_04_textarea": "", "pb_05_textarea": "", "pb_06_textarea": "https://ongcindia.com/documents/77751/1767719/4994_248_Amcobm.pdf/9c5b3c75-de33-855a-5cd5-40ae9a8cf18b\\nhttps://ongcindia.com/documents/77751/1767719/5151_336_CDA+Rules.pdf/2425e811-54e7-435b-031e-43d482fa2be9", "pb_07_textarea": "https://ongcindia.com/documents/77751/0/Policy202.pdf/40017d6c-4d54-f318-eeac-a87dba556024", "pb_08_textarea": "ONGC has a dedicated Carbon Management & Sustainability Group, which is headed by Director (Exploration).\\nThe group not found to be board level.", "pb_09_textarea": "", "pb_10_textarea": "Yes, ONGC has an anti-bribery policy. The policy covers the whole organization, the employees, stakeholders and business associates. It highlights compliance with laws and regulations, establishment of management systems explaining the consequences of being non-compliant as well as for setting, reviewing and achieving compay’s objectives. ONGC is also committed to continual improvement of its governance of Ethics, Transparency and Accountability while being in tuned with Department of Public Enterprises (DPE), SEBI and other applicable guidelines of the Govt. of India. \\n\\nWeblink for the policy- https://ongcindia.com/documents/77751/1767719/3006_316_wb30052019.pdf/f57e9f93-0ede-8e52-007c-ffdaccb117b0 \\n\\nThe Company has following policies or guidelines which aid Ethics, Transparency and Accountability in conduct of its operations:\\na. Code of Conducts for Directors and Senior Management Personnel;\\nb. Book of Delegated Powers;\\nc. Manuals, such as, Integrated Materials Management Manual, Finance Manual, CSR Manual, etc.\\nd. Risk Policy containing risk framework and register containing identified risk areas and its mitigation\\nplans, managed and monitored by an independent Enterprise Risk Management Cell (ERM)\\n\\nhttps://ongcindia.com/documents/77751/2660534/abmseng230623.pdf", "pb_11_textarea": "", "pb_12_textarea": "No sustainable sourcing policy", "pb_13_textarea": "", "pb_14_textarea": "", "pb_15_textarea": "The Company has introduced several policies and facilities aimed at supporting people with disabilities (PWD). To encourage their participation, various programs focused their empowerment and development have been organized throughout the Company. Weblink for the policy is https://ongcindia.com/documents/77751/2660534/policy310723.pdf/eda414a7-dc4f-8704-07bc-9ebd25d409f7", "pb_16_textarea": "", "pb_17_textarea": "", "pb_18_textarea": "", "pb_19_textarea": "Coverage: 100%\\n\\nSafety studies like Hazard Identification (HAZID), Hazard Operability (HAZOP), Quantitative Risk Assessment (QRA) and Safety Integrity Level (SIL) are conducted at inception stage of all E&P projects. All jobs are carried out after conducting Job Safety Analysis (JSA). Toolbox Talk (TBT) is carried out before start of work in every shift. Along with everything, Internal Safety Audits (ISAs) are also conducted to assess and check the efficacy of safety measures. Oil Industry Safety Directorate (OISD), Directorate General of Mines Safety (DGMS) and Directorate of Industrial Safety and Health (DISH) conduct regularly Audits/ Inspections to check the compliances of respective rules/ regulations. The hazards associated with each operational activity are captured in Installation specific risk register in accordance with guidelines of ISO 17776: 2000.The. Based on the  associated risk, site specific safe working practices/plans are developed and implemented.\\n\\nYes\\n\\nYes", "pb_20_textarea": "", "pb_21_textarea": "", "pb_22_textarea": "", "pb_23_textarea": "", "pb_24_textarea": "", "pb_25_textarea": "", "pb_26_textarea": "Yes", "pb_27_textarea": "", "pb_28_textarea": "converted for per crore rupee of turnover\\nYes, Bureau Veritas", "pb_29_textarea": "converted for per crore rupee of turnover\\nYes, Bureau Veritas", "pb_30_textarea": "converted for per crore rupee of turnover\\nYes, Bureau Veritas", "pb_31_textarea": "converted for per crore rupee of turnover\\nYes, Bureau Veritas", "pb_32_textarea": "CHanges data based on note: \\"Note: Figure reported as % of total eligible purchase. However the total procurement from MSEs was 11.85% out of the total purchase.\\"\\n2023 fig no provided in note. hence not entered.", "pb_33_textarea": "Total procurement from MSEs for the fiscal year 2023-24 was 58.6% of annual eligible procurement including 0.84% from Women\\nMSEs and 0.50% from SC/ST MSEs. However the total procurement from MSEs was 11.85% out of the total purchase. \\n", "pb_34_textarea": "", "pb_35_textarea": "https://reports.ongc.co.in/group/reports_en/home/virtualcorporate/services/chief-information-s