144	138	\N	Financial Services	{"pb_01": "information_available", "pb_02": "information_available", "pb_03": "information_available", "pb_04": "information_available", "pb_05": "information_available", "pb_06": "Information Available", "pb_07": "Information available", "pb_08": "information_available", "pb_09": "Information available", "pb_10": "information_available", "pb_11": "information_available", "pb_12": "Indicator is not relevant for the industry", "pb_13": "No LCA conducted", "pb_14": "information_available", "pb_15": "information_available", "pb_16": "information_available", "pb_17": "information_available", "pb_18": "information_available", "pb_19": "information_available", "pb_20": "information_available", "pb_21": "No information", "pb_22": "information_available", "pb_23": "information_available", "pb_24": "information_available", "pb_25": "information_available", "pb_26": "information_available", "pb_27": "information_available", "pb_28": "information_available", "pb_29": "information_available", "pb_30": "information_available", "pb_31": "information_available", "pb_32": "information_available", "pb_33": "No clear information", "pb_34": "Indicator is not relevant for the industry", "pb_35": "information_available", "pb_01_textarea": "", "pb_02_textarea": "", "pb_03_textarea": "", "pb_04_textarea": "", "pb_05_textarea": "", "pb_06_textarea": "https://www.federalbank.co.in/documents/10180/816529059/FINAL+CG+CODE+FY24.pdf/8ec158ef-e145-76e8-642b-26e23f6ccb66?t=1713416946738", "pb_07_textarea": "https://www.federalbank.co.in/documents/10180/45777/Environmental%2C+Social+and+Governance+%28ESG%29+Policy.pdf/5eb32c8d-41ac-fbca-25d3-40a0e0180785?t=1683266571942", "pb_08_textarea": "Damodaran C (Chief Risk officer) - The Risk Management Committee (RMC) of the Board oversees Environmental, Social and Governance (ESG) aspects in both its own operations and lending operations. All the policies related to ESG/ESMS are approved by the Board. The risks associated with the lending operation are duly factored under ESMS policy and ESG Policy assesses the organization’s business practices and performance on various sustainability and ethical issues. Bank is also having an executive-level E&S committee headed by MD&CEO which oversees both ESG and ESMS aspects and reports to RMC of the Board.", "pb_09_textarea": "", "pb_10_textarea": "The Bank has a comprehensive Anti-Bribery and Corruption policy which establishes comprehensive, consistent and effective standards that are to be adhered to in the conduct of Bank’s day-to-day operations. The policy can be accessed through the following link: https://www.federalbank.co.in/documents/10180/45777/Policy+on+Anti+-+Bribery+and+Corruption+%28ABC%29.pdf/10c35a9d-7265-7791-6bd6-d165e648f34a?t=1672122690405", "pb_11_textarea": "", "pb_12_textarea": "The Bank has formulated a supplier code of conduct that requires suppliers to adhere to laws related to human rights, labor, health and safety, sustainability, environment, and ethics. The Bank has a board-approved Sustainable Procurement Policy, which guides all procurement decisions and processes. Currently, the Bank does not capture the details of vendors who are certified under various environmental standards.\\nSustainable procurement policy ensures that we procure goods and services that are environmentally and socially sustainable. As we progress in our ESG journey, we will make efforts to capture data on sustainable suppliers.", "pb_13_textarea": "", "pb_14_textarea": "", "pb_15_textarea": "The Bank is committed to fostering diversity, equity, and inclusion as a culture that enables all employees to bring their authentic selves to work and to fully participate with their knowledge, experience, and viewpoint to provide incomparable value for all stakeholders. The Bank also recognises that each employee has varying access to resources and privileges and is working towards taking steps to ensure that every employee is provided with the unique resources they need to have access to opportunities at a given organisation. The diversity, equity, and inclusion policy (the ‘DE&I policy’) aims to set out Federal Bank’s commitment to providing a workplace free from discrimination for employees. The policy also sets out Bank’s expectations, where each employee is responsible for adhering to and upholding the policy. The policy can be accessed at Diversity, equity and inclusion policy - https://www.federalbank.co.in/documents/10180/45777/Diversity%2C+Equity+%26+Inclusion+Policy.pdf/a7d0b3d5-dc0d-7485-a5ec-7ca4aba5eb23?t=1683351345782", "pb_16_textarea": "", "pb_17_textarea": "", "pb_18_textarea": "", "pb_19_textarea": "Considering the nature of the business, occupational health and safety risks are quite limited. While the Bank is developing an exhaustive Occupational Health and Safety Management System, many steps have been taken for improvement of workplace safety and the elimination of possible workplace injury and illness. The Bank has adopted a Business Continuity Management System accredited through ISO 22301. Detailed SOPs are issued on the Dos and Don’ts to ensure the safety and wellbeing of all its employees. The steps taken by the Bank in this regard are:\\n• Periodic training on fire safety, firefighting and evacuation.\\n• Periodic training on handling medical emergencies, in partnership with reputed hospitals.\\n• Nomination of an Emergency Response Team for each location.\\n• Deployment of access control measures and physical guarding as per risk assessment.\\n• Periodic communications to employees for creating awareness on OHS aspects.\\n• Advisories regarding adverse weather situations and action to be taken to safeguard own life and assets.\\n• Regular conduct of Fire and evacuation drills at all locations\\n\\nThough work-related hazards are minimal considering the nature of business, the Bank has put in place risk mitigation measures which include –\\n• Access control systems for administrative offices and highly secure facilities.\\n• CCTV linked to a Central Remote Monitoring Centre which carries out e-surveillance 24x7.\\n• Physical Security.\\n• Fire alarm system consisting of smoke and heat detectors and alert mechanism.\\n The Bank has SLAs in place with all vendors to ensure regular preventive maintenance and health check-up. In addition, the Bank has nominated employees comprising the Emergency Response Team (ERT) for each location who are responsible for reporting work-related hazards, if any. Advisories on various safety related aspects including weather warnings are issued from time to time.", "pb_20_textarea": "", "pb_21_textarea": "They carry out electrical safety inspections of all their premises through professional third-party agencies once every two years. During the past two years, the Bank has conducted electrical inspections at 1322 locations. Corrective actions in the form of rectification works are performed on the premises whenever required. ", "pb_22_textarea": "", "pb_23_textarea": "", "pb_24_textarea": "", "pb_25_textarea": "", "pb_26_textarea": "https://www.federalbank.co.in/documents/10180/45777/Supplier+Code+of+Conduct.pdf/fb0782e3-ff2a-5ba0-1586-a1abb3472e9c?t=1715587458177", "pb_27_textarea": "", "pb_28_textarea": "Reasonable assurance undertaken by Bureau Veritas Industrial Services (India) Pvt for the indicator for FY 2023-24.", "pb_29_textarea": "Reasonable assurance undertaken by Bureau Veritas Industrial Services (India) Pvt for the indicator for FY 2023-24.", "pb_30_textarea": "Reasonable assurance undertaken by Bureau Veritas Industrial Services (India) Pvt for the indicator for FY 2023-24", "pb_31_textarea": "Reasonable assurance undertaken by Bureau Veritas Industrial Services (India) Pvt for the indicator for FY 2023-24", "pb_32_textarea": "", "pb_33_textarea": "A preferential procurement process is not implemented by the Bank. As a Financial Institution, their inputs are primarily in the form of technological infrastructure, platforms and services. Thus, the Procurement Policy of the Bank focuses on the ability of the service provider/ supplier to adhere to the standards/requirements set by the Bank. However, 100% of the consumables/ stationery required for day-to-day\\nactivities at the branches/ offices are purchased locally. They have a sustainable procurement policy, which guides their procurement practices", "pb_34_textarea": "", "pb_35_textarea": "", "pb_07_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_08_option_radio": "ESG/Sustainability function part of other board committee", "pb_10_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_13_percentage_1": "", "pb_13_percentage_2": "", "pb_15_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_19_option_radio": "Company has OHS management system & process to identify risks", "pb_26_option_radio": "Yes, it does", "pb_35_option_radio": "Internal Policy", "pb_06_option1_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_12_option_number": "", "pb_33_option_number": "", "pb_02_option_number1": "12", "pb_02_option_number2": "", "pb_03_option_number1": "18.19", "pb_03_option_number2": "20.0", "pb_28_option_checkbox": "Independent assessment/ evaluation/assurance has been carried out by an external agency", "pb_29_option_checkbox": "Independent assessment/ evaluation/assurance has been carried out by an external agency", "pb_30_option_checkbox": "Independent assessment/ evaluation/assurance has been carried out by an external agency", "pb_31_option_checkbox": "Independent assessment/ evaluation/assurance has been carried out by an external agency", "pb_05_option_checkbox1": "Employees", "pb_05_option_checkbox2": "Workers", "pb_05_option_checkbox3": "Communities", "pb_05_option_checkbox4": "Value chain partners", "pb_05_option_checkbox5": "Customers", "pb_13_option_checkbox2": "", "pb_24_option1_checkbox": "", "pb_06_option1_checkbox1": "Code of conduct for Board of Directors/KMPs", "pb_06_option2_checkbox2": "", "pb_14_option1_checkbox1": "", 