g with the anti-bribery policy is disseminated to all the employees, customers, vendors and other stakeholders. The policy is available in the company’s website https://esabindia.com/in/ind_en/investor-relationship/policies/anti-bribery-policy/ and Business Condict guidelines on https://esab.com/mv/ind_en/investor-relationship/policies/code-of-business-conduct/", "pb_11_textarea": "", "pb_12_textarea": "", "pb_13_textarea": "", "pb_14_textarea": "", "pb_15_textarea": "Though there is no separate policy, ESAB India Ltd. is an equal opportunity employer encouraging diversity in the workplace.", "pb_16_textarea": "", "pb_17_textarea": "", "pb_18_textarea": "", "pb_19_textarea": "Yes, ESAB India Limited has implemented an Occupational Health and Safety management system, certifiable to ISO 45001, across all its locations. The commitment to maintaining, fostering, and continually improving the safety and well-being of employees is embedded in the company's wider risk management and control processes.\\n\\nAs part of the implementation of ISO standards, procedures for Hazard Identification and Risk Assessment (HIRA) have been established and implemented across the business units. HIRA is conducted for both routine and non-routine activities. Individuals involved in operations, EHS officers, and contractor representatives (where applicable) identify work-related hazards. The identified hazards are recorded, and control measures are discussed and defined according to the hierarchy of controls. The Corrective and Preventive Action (CAPA) tracker is employed to proactively identify safety risks in high-risk activities and implement engineering controls to mitigate these risks. A Cross-Functional Team reviews high-risk activities and implements engineering controls where feasible to mitigate risks. Focused training sessions on \\"Behavioral Based Safety\\" (BBS) are conducted to raise awareness among third-party and contractor employees, promoting the adoption of safe work practices.\\n\\nYes\\n\\nYes", "pb_20_textarea": "", "pb_21_textarea": "", "pb_22_textarea": "", "pb_23_textarea": "", "pb_24_textarea": "", "pb_25_textarea": "", "pb_26_textarea": "", "pb_27_textarea": "", "pb_28_textarea": "", "pb_29_textarea": "", "pb_30_textarea": "", "pb_31_textarea": "They will be monitoring and reporting the Scope 3 emissions going forward.", "pb_32_textarea": "", "pb_33_textarea": "Reason sited - No, contracts are awarded on merit and not on preference.", "pb_34_textarea": "", "pb_35_textarea": "http://esabindia.com/in/ind_en/privacy-policy/", "pb_07_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_08_option_radio": "No board level committee, but CSO or dedicated executive director for sustainability issues", "pb_10_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_13_percentage_1": "", "pb_13_percentage_2": "", "pb_15_option_radio": "Company has no such policy in place", "pb_19_option_radio": "Company has OHS management system, process to identify & process to report risks", "pb_26_option_radio": "Yes, it does", "pb_35_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_06_option1_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_06_option2_radio": "Internal Policy", "pb_12_option_number": "80.0", "pb_33_option_number": "", "pb_02_option_number1": "", "pb_02_option_number2": "", "pb_03_option_number1": "16.67", "pb_03_option_number2": "0", "pb_28_option_checkbox": "", "pb_29_option_checkbox": "", "pb_30_option_checkbox": "", "pb_31_option_checkbox": "", "pb_05_option_checkbox1": "Employees", "pb_05_option_checkbox2": "Workers", "pb_05_option_checkbox3": "", "pb_05_option_checkbox4": "Value chain partners", "pb_05_option_checkbox5": "Customers", "pb_13_option_checkbox2": "", "pb_24_option1_checkbox": "", "pb_06_option1_checkbox1": "Code of conduct for Board of Directors/KMPs", "pb_06_option2_checkbox2": "", "pb_14_option1_checkbox1": "", "pb_20_option1_checkbox1": "Lost Time Injury Frequency Rate", "pb_20_option1_checkbox2": "Fatalities", "pb_01_table_row1_num