150	162	\N	Automobiles & Auto Components	{"pb_01": "information_available", "pb_02": "information_available", "pb_03": "information_available", "pb_04": "information_available", "pb_05": "information_available", "pb_06": "Information Available", "pb_07": "Information available", "pb_08": "information_available", "pb_09": "Information available", "pb_10": "information_available", "pb_11": "information_available", "pb_12": "information_available", "pb_13": "LCA conducted", "pb_14": "information_available", "pb_15": "information_available", "pb_16": "information_available", "pb_17": "information_available", "pb_18": "information_available", "pb_19": "information_available", "pb_20": "information_available", "pb_21": "information_available", "pb_22": "information_available", "pb_23": "information_available", "pb_24": "information_available", "pb_25": "information_available", "pb_26": "information_available", "pb_27": "information_available", "pb_28": "information_available", "pb_29": "information_available", "pb_30": "information_available", "pb_31": "No information", "pb_32": "information_available", "pb_33": "No clear information", "pb_34": "information_available", "pb_35": "information_available", "pb_01_textarea": "", "pb_02_textarea": "", "pb_03_textarea": "", "pb_04_textarea": "", "pb_05_textarea": "The Company has a specific e-mail ID earmarked for receiving investor complaints, which is investorrelations@aisglass.com. Details of investor complaints received by\\nthe Company are filed on a quarterly basis with the Stock Exchanges where the Company’s shares are listed. https://www.aisglass.com/forinvestors/ investor-relations-contact/. ", "pb_06_textarea": "https://www.aisglass.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/ais_policies.pdf", "pb_07_textarea": "AIS strongly promotes “equal opportunity to all”, irrespective of gender, caste, creed, religion, disability, sexual orientation, personal characteristic or status and any other discriminatory factor. Company's “Policy on Equal Opportunity & Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion’, recognizes the value of a diverse workforce. The Policy is \\n ommitted to provide equal opportunities in employment and fostering an inclusive workplace where all employees are treated with respect, equality, and dignity. In addition, salient features of our Human Rights Policy includes non-discrimination, equal opportunities, reasonable accommodations, accessibility, awareness,\\nand sensitization factors, along with grievance redressal mechanism.  ", "pb_08_textarea": "The CSR Committee of the Board, inter alia, reviews, monitors, and provides strategic direction to the Company’s CSR and sustainability practices and ensures that they are fulfilling its outlined objectives. The Committee seeks to guide the Company in crafting unique models to support creation of sustainable livelihoods together with environmental regeneration. The Committee also reviews the Business Responsibility and Sustainability Report of the Company and recommends the same to the Board for adoptionand approves the Annual Report of the Company.", "pb_09_textarea": "", "pb_10_textarea": "The AIS Code of Conduct expresses the Company's commitment to ‘Anti-Corruption and Anti-Bribery practices’ with the following statement: “Our employees and representatives, including agents and intermediaries, shall not directly or indirectly offer or accept any illegal or improper payments or similar benefits intended or perceived to gain undue advantage in business\\ndealings at AIS.” AlS's Code of Conduct is available: https://www.aisglass.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/Code_of Conduct for Directors -and Senior Management.pdf. \\n", "pb_11_textarea": "R&D not applicable to AIS.", "pb_12_textarea": "", "pb_13_textarea": "", "pb_14_textarea": "", "pb_15_textarea": "AIS strongly promotes \\"equal opportunity to all\\", irrespective of gender, caste, creed, religion, disability,  sexual orientation, personal characterstic of status and any other discriminatoy factor. Company's \\"Policy on Equal Opportunity & Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion\\", recognizes the values of diverse workforce. The Policy is commited to provide equal opportunities in employment and fostering an inclusive workplace where all employees are treated with respect, equality, and dignity. In addition, salient features of our Human Rights Policy includes non-discrimination, equal opportunities, reasonable accommodations, accessibility,  awareness, and sensitization factors, along with grieveance redressal mechanism.", "pb_16_textarea": "", "pb_17_textarea": "", "pb_18_textarea": "", "pb_19_textarea": "AIS has implemented a robust “Health and Safety Management” system. It is the formal, top-down, organizationwide approach for managing safety risks and ensuring the effectiveness of safety controls. It includes policies, systematic procedures, and practices for managing safety risks, and reducing accidents and occupational hazards and illnesses at the workplace.\\n\\nAIS Safety system has been broadly classified into two categories:\\n1. Process Safety & Human Safety\\n2. Fire Safety, Electrical fire safety & Water Safety\\nIn addition to this, Occupational Health & Safety Activities are as given below:\\n• Pre-employment and Periodical Medical Assessments\\n• Health & Safety Training\\n• Safety Study and Audits\\n• Work Permit System\\n• Contractor Safety Management\\n• Occupational Health & Safety Communication\\n• Emergency Preparedness\\n• Incident Investigation\\n• Safety awareness and vaccination programmes.\\n• MI UC/ UA App for reporting safety incidents and risk across plants, pilot initiated at Bawal plant in FY 2023 - 24\\nFeedback received from the outcome of risk assessment, suggestions, Investigation process, behaviour-based safety observations, audit outcomes etc. are recorded and monitored as part of continual improvement at AIS.\\n\\nThe Company undertakes periodic internal and external audits to ensure compliance with the Occupational Health and Safety management system within the manufacturing operations. EHS training, audits and inspections are carried out as per the guidelines of the ISO 45001 standard. The Company’s Process Safety Management system facilitates the implementation of best safety practices. Further, it enables the identification of work-related hazards through design checklists, Hazard, and Operability Analysis (HAZOP), Hazard Identification and Risk Assessment (HIRA), and other consequence modelling studies.\\n•\\tRoutine activities are monitored through adherence to Job Safety Analysis, Hazard Identification and Risk Assessment (HIRA), Standard Operating procedure, and Operational Control Procedure.\\n•\\tNon-routine activities are monitored through Work Permit systems and JSA (Job Safety Analysis) to ensure the health and safety of workers. Machines and Materials are, a) Hot work permit, b) Confined space entry permit, c) Height work permit, d) General work permit, e) Electrical work permit, f) Lifting work permits, and g) Excavation work permit.\\n\\nYes\\n\\nYes", "pb_20_textarea": "", "pb_21_textarea": "", "pb_22_textarea": "", "pb_23_textarea": "", "pb_24_textarea": "", "pb_25_textarea": "", "pb_26_textarea": "", "pb_27_textarea": "", "pb_28_textarea": "", "pb_29_textarea": "false", "pb_30_textarea": "", "pb_31_textarea": "AIS has initiated the process of collecting and developing the inventory for Scope- 3.", "pb_32_textarea": "", "pb_33_textarea": "", "pb_34_textarea": "", "pb_35_textarea": "AIS has an Information Security and Management (ISMs) Policy that is based on ISO 27001 Standards and GDPR framework. Further, the IT system at AIS is BCP complaint i.e., the Company’s information security aspects of business continuity and Disaster Recovery management follows the cardinals of Risk-based thinking (RBT), process approach, and the PDCA (Plan-Do-Check-Act) methodology. ", "pb_07_option_radio": "Internal Policy", "pb_08_option_radio": "Dedicated Board ESG/Sustainability committee", "pb_10_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_13_percentage_1": "", "pb_13_percentage_2": "100", "pb_15_option_radio": "Internal Policy", "pb_19_option_radio": "Company has OHS management system, process to identify & process to report risks", "pb_26_option_radio": "Yes, it does", "pb_35_option_radio": "Internal Policy", "pb_06_option1_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_12_option_number": "100.0", "pb_33_option_number": "0.0", "pb_02_option_number1": "2", "pb_02_option_number2": "0", "pb_03_option_number1": "33.34", "pb_03_option_number2": "0.0", "pb_28_option_checkbox": "", "pb_29_option_checkbox": "", "pb_30_option_checkbox": "", "pb_31_option_checkbox": "", "pb_05_option_checkbox1": "Employees", "pb_05_option_checkbox2": "Workers", "pb_05_option_checkbox3": "Communities", "pb_05_option_checkbox4": "Value chain partners", "pb_05_option_checkbox5": "Customers", "pb_13_option_checkbox2": "", "pb_24_option1_checkbox": "", "pb_06_option1_checkbox1": "Code of conduct for Board of Directors/KMPs", "pb_06_option2_checkbox2": "", "pb_14_option1_checkbox1": "", "pb_20_option1_checkbox1": "Lost Time Injury Frequency Rate", "pb_20_option1_checkbox2": "Fatalities", "pb_01_table_row1_number1": "95.11", "pb_01_table_row1_number2": "4.9", "pb_01_table_row1_number3": "100.0", "pb_01_table_row1_number4": "0.0", "pb_01_table_row2_number1": "100.0", "pb_01_table_row2_number2": "0.0", "pb_01_table_row2_number3": "94.0", "pb_01_table_row2_number4": "6.01", "pb_01_table_row3_number1": "95.17", "pb_01_table_row3_number2": "4.84", "pb_01_table_row3_number3": "94.89", "pb_01_table_row3_number4": "5.12", "pb_04_table_row1_number1": "18.0", "pb_04_table_row1_number2": "16.0", "pb_04_table_row1_number3": "14.0", "pb_04_table_row2_number1": "29.0", "pb_04_table_row2_number2": "31.0", "pb_04_table_row2_number3": "31.0", "pb_04_table_row3_number1": "19.0", "pb_04_table_row3_number2": "16.0", "pb_04_table_row3_number3": "15.0", "pb_04_table_row4_number1": "0.0", "pb_