155	164	\N	Healthcare	{"pb_01": "information_available", "pb_02": "information_available", "pb_03": "information_available", "pb_04": "information_available", "pb_05": "information_available", "pb_06": "Information Available", "pb_07": "Information available", "pb_08": "information_available", "pb_09": "Information available", "pb_10": "information_available", "pb_11": "information_available", "pb_12": "information_available", "pb_13": "No information", "pb_14": "information_available", "pb_15": "information_available", "pb_16": "information_available", "pb_17": "information_available", "pb_18": "information_available", "pb_19": "information_available", "pb_20": "information_available", "pb_21": "information_available", "pb_22": "information_available", "pb_23": "information_available", "pb_24": "information_available", "pb_25": "information_available", "pb_26": "information_available", "pb_27": "information_available", "pb_28": "information_available", "pb_29": "information_available", "pb_30": "information_available", "pb_31": "No information", "pb_32": "information_available", "pb_33": "No clear information", "pb_34": "information_available", "pb_35": "information_available", "pb_01_textarea": "", "pb_02_textarea": "", "pb_03_textarea": "", "pb_04_textarea": "", "pb_05_textarea": "https://www.aurobindo.com/api/uploads/disclosure_under_regulation/Whistle%20Blower%20Policy-APL-New-March2024.pdf", "pb_06_textarea": "https://www.aurobindo.com/api/uploads/Policy%20on%20Business%20Ethics%20&%20Values_Aurobindo%20Pharma%20Ltd.pdf", "pb_07_textarea": "https://www.aurobindo.com/pdfs/Human%20Rights%20Policy_Aurobindo%20Pharma%20Ltd.pdf", "pb_08_textarea": "ESG and Sustainability Committee\\nName of the director\\tDIN Number\\tDesignation\\nMrs. Savita Mahajan\\t06492679\\tChairperson\\nMr. M.Ramasubramanian Kumar\\t03628755\\tMember\\nMr. Santanu Mukherjee\\t07716452\\tMember\\nMr. K. Nithyananda Reddy\\t01284195\\tMember\\nMr. M. Madan Mohan Reddy\\t01284266\\tMember", "pb_09_textarea": "", "pb_10_textarea": "https://www.aurobindo.com/api/uploads/Policy%20on%20Business%20Ethics%20&%20Values_Aurobindo%20Pharma%20Ltd.pdf", "pb_11_textarea": "", "pb_12_textarea": "", "pb_13_textarea": "", "pb_14_textarea": "", "pb_15_textarea": "https://www.aurobindo.com/pdfs/Human%20Rights%20Policy_Aurobindo%20Pharma%20Ltd.pdf", "pb_16_textarea": "", "pb_17_textarea": "", "pb_18_textarea": "", "pb_19_textarea": "Yes. The company has implemented an Occupational health and safety management system. The coverage is 100% of our facilities, and it covers both regular employees and contractors.\\nHealth, safety, and well-being of employees and associates are a crucial material topic for the company. The company is committed towards instilling a healthy lifestyle, a safe working environment, and a healthy work-life balance. EHS framework and management practices assure compliance while prioritising product and process safety and safeguarding all employees. Each manufacturing facility has departmental and Apex safety committee. Every month Management review meetings are conducted which comprises top management from Corporate and representatives from all sites including site heads  to examine safety performance and streamline operational procedures critical to safety requirements.\\nHealth and safety training is provided to both permanent and contractual workers, ensuring that our team understands the significance of safe procedures and guidelines. Risk identification and assessments are undertaken as part of the process before scaling up. Before commencing any chemical process in the manufacturing area, a hazard and operability study (HAZOP) is conducted. For all new projects, existing production units, and distribution centres among others, the Company observes and monitors the safety laws and procedures.\\n\\nThe company has developed a corporate guidance document which provides the course on how to identify, evaluate occupational Health and Safety risks, and reduce them to an acceptable level by strengthening existing controls and/ or incorporating additional controls for all the activities within the facilities of the organization. The Company undertakes periodic internal audits to ensure the compliance of Occupational Health and Safety management system within the manufacturing operation. The EHS trainings, audits and inspections are carried out as per the corporate guidelines. Further, it enables the identification of work-related hazards through design checklists, Hazard and Operability Analysis (HAZOP), Hazard Identification and Risk Assessment (HIRA), Activity based Risk Assessment. \\nThe guidelines clearly outline the role and responsibilities of individuals directly involved in identifying and mitigating Health & Safety risks on routine and non-routine basis.\\n\\nYes\\n\\nYes", "pb_20_textarea": "", "pb_21_textarea": "", "pb_22_textarea": "", "pb_23_textarea": "", "pb_24_textarea": "", "pb_25_textarea": "", "pb_26_textarea": "human rights requirements form part of business agreements and contracts on\\nneed basis", "pb_27_textarea": "", "pb_28_textarea": "true", "pb_29_textarea": "true", "pb_30_textarea": "true", "pb_31_textarea": "", "pb_32_textarea": "", "pb_33_textarea": "", "pb_34_textarea": "", "pb_35_textarea": "Policy on cyber security is available to address risks related to information security and data privacy.", "pb_07_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_08_option_radio": "Dedicated Board ESG/Sustainability committee", "pb_10_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_13_percentage_1": "", "pb_13_percentage_2": "", "pb_15_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_19_option_radio": "Company has OHS management system, process to identify & process to report risks", "pb_26_option_radio": "Yes, it does", "pb_35_option_radio": "Internal Policy", "pb_06_option1_radio": "Internal Policy", "pb_06_option2_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_12_option_number": "100.0", "pb_33_op