167	186	\N	Capital Goods	{"pb_01": "information_available", "pb_02": "information_available", "pb_03": "information_available", "pb_04": "information_available", "pb_05": "information_available", "pb_06": "Information Available", "pb_07": "Information available", "pb_08": "information_available", "pb_09": "Information available", "pb_10": "information_available", "pb_11": "information_available", "pb_12": "information_available", "pb_13": "No LCA conducted", "pb_14": "information_available", "pb_15": "information_available", "pb_16": "information_available", "pb_17": "information_available", "pb_18": "information_available", "pb_19": "information_available", "pb_20": "information_available", "pb_21": "information_available", "pb_22": "information_available", "pb_23": "information_available", "pb_24": "information_available", "pb_25": "information_available", "pb_26": "information_available", "pb_27": "information_available", "pb_28": "information_available", "pb_29": "information_available", "pb_30": "information_available", "pb_31": "No information", "pb_32": "information_available", "pb_33": "No clear information", "pb_34": "information_available", "pb_35": "information_available", "pb_01_textarea": "", "pb_02_textarea": "", "pb_03_textarea": "", "pb_04_textarea": "", "pb_05_textarea": "https://borosilrenewables.com/Files/Stakeholder%20Engagement%20and%20Grievance%20Redressal%20Policy.pdf\\n", "pb_06_textarea": "https://borosilrenewables.com/Files/Code%20of%20Conduct.pdf", "pb_07_textarea": " https://borosilrenewables.com/Files/Human-Rights-Policy-revised.pdf\\n", "pb_08_textarea": "Yes, the Company has established Environment, Social & Governance (ESG) Committee to facilitate decision making on sustainability related matters. The primary objective of this ESG Committee is to assist the Board in realizing the ESG commitments of the Company. The Committee assumes overall responsibility for the following key aspects:\\n1) Endorsing the ESG vision and continually setting goals in line with that vision.\\n2) Monitoring the progress towards achieving the stated vision and goals.\\n3) Reviewing and addressing any statutory performance obligations related to Sustainability/ESG. \\n\\nAdditionally, the Committee’s responsibilities include other items/matters prescribed under applicable laws or directed by the Board to ensure compliance with relevant regulations. The Committee also plays a crucial role in reporting the progress of various initiatives and ensuring timely and appropriate disclosures on a periodic basis.", "pb_09_textarea": "", "pb_10_textarea": "https://borosilrenewables.com/Files/Anti-Bribery%20and%20Anti-Corruption%20Policy.pdf", "pb_11_textarea": "", "pb_12_textarea": "", "pb_13_textarea": "", "pb_14_textarea": "", "pb_15_textarea": "policy:https://borosilrenewables.com/Files/Equal%20Opportunity,%20Diversity%20&%20Inclusion%20Policy.pdf", "pb_16_textarea": "", "pb_17_textarea": "", "pb_18_textarea": "", "pb_19_textarea": "The Company has occupational health and safety management system at its plant. The plant is certified with ISO certification for Occupational Health and Safety Management and for Environment Management System. Fire safety equipment like fire and smoke detectors, fire extinguishers & sprinklers are installed at plant premises. Maintenance of these installations is conducted at regular intervals and maintenance contracts are in place. Fire drills are conducted regularly to raise fire safety awareness. Drinking water is tested every six months by approved laboratories, and air quality checks are performed annually. Each plant is equipped with a first aid box for medical needs, and wheelchairs and foldable stretchers are available for emergencies. Emergency contact numbers for police stations, ambulances, hospitals, and building management are prominently displayed at each workstation.\\n\\nThe company has a comprehensive mechanism to identify work-related hazards and assess risks on a routine basis. For routine activities, a Hazard Identification and Risk Assessment (HIRA) system is in place for all processes. For non-routine activities, a work permit system is implemented, and risk assessments are conducted before commencing such work. This process includes identifying risks during shop floor visits by safety teams, daily briefings, and periodic meetings with employees and workers to gather their feedback. The workforce at each facility is actively involved in identifying and mitigating work-related hazards.\\n\\nYes\\n\\nYes", "pb_20_textarea": "", "pb_21_textarea": "", "pb_22_textarea": "", "pb_23_textarea": "", "pb_24_textarea": "", "pb_25_textarea": "", "pb_26_textarea": "No", "pb_27_textarea": "", "pb_28_textarea": "false", "pb_29_textarea": "true", "pb_30_textarea": "false", "pb_31_textarea": "", "pb_32_textarea": "", "pb_33_textarea": "", "pb_34_textarea": "", "pb_35_textarea": "https://borosilrenewables.com/Files/Data Privacy Policy.pdf", "pb_07_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_08_option_radio": "Dedicated Board ESG/Sustainability committee", "pb_10_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_13_percentage_1": "", "pb_13_percentage_2": "", "pb_15_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_19_option_radio": "Company has OHS management system, process to identify & process to report risks", "pb_26_option_radio": "No it doesn’t", "pb_35_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_06_option1_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_06_option2_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_12_option_number": "91.67", "pb_33_option_number": "", "pb_02_option_number1": "12", "pb_02_option_number2": "9", "pb_03_option_number1": "11.12", "pb_03_option_number2": "0.0", "pb_28_option_checkbox": "", "pb_29_option_checkbox": "Independent assessment/ evaluation/assurance has been carried out by an external agency", "pb_30_option_checkbox": "", "pb_31_option_checkbox": "", "pb_05_option_checkbox1": "Employees", "pb_05_option_checkbox2": "Workers"