191	210	\N	Information Technology	{"pb_01": "information_available", "pb_02": "information_available", "pb_03": "information_available", "pb_04": "information_available", "pb_05": "information_available", "pb_06": "Information Available", "pb_07": "Information available", "pb_08": "information_available", "pb_09": "No clear information", "pb_10": "information_available", "pb_11": "information_available", "pb_12": "information_available", "pb_13": "No information", "pb_14": "information_available", "pb_15": "information_available", "pb_16": "information_available", "pb_17": "information_available", "pb_18": "information_available", "pb_19": "information_available", "pb_20": "information_available", "pb_21": "information_available", "pb_22": "information_available", "pb_23": "information_available", "pb_24": "information_available", "pb_25": "information_available", "pb_26": "information_available", "pb_27": "information_available", "pb_28": "No information", "pb_29": "information_available", "pb_30": "information_available", "pb_31": "information_available", "pb_32": "information_available", "pb_33": "information_available", "pb_34": "Indicator is not relevant for the industry", "pb_35": "information_available", "pb_01_textarea": "", "pb_02_textarea": "", "pb_03_textarea": "", "pb_04_textarea": "", "pb_05_textarea": "https://www.kpit.com/documents/vigil-mechanism-whistle-blower-policy/", "pb_06_textarea": "https://d1rz4ui464s6g7.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/29171238/Code-of-conduct-Policy.pdf", "pb_07_textarea": "", "pb_08_textarea": "In KPIT, all the sustainability aspects are overseen by the CSR Committee. Composition of CSR committee is as follows:\\n\\nSr. No.\\tName of the Director\\tPosition held in CSR Committee\\n1\\tMr. Anant Talaulicar\\tChairman\\n2\\tMr. S. B. (Ravi) Pandit\\tMember\\n3\\tMr. Sachin Tikekar\\t              Member", "pb_09_textarea": "", "pb_10_textarea": "KPIT strictly follows ‘Zero Tolerance” against corruption and bribery. KPIT’s Code of Conduct and Vendor Code of Conduct comprehensively addresses anti-corruption and anti-bribery measures, unequivocally asserting the Company’s stance of non-tolerance towards such practices. The Company expressly prohibits all employees, directors, associates, suppliers, and third-party vendors from engaging in any form of bribery or offering anything of value to obtain or retain business for KPIT or in connection with business operations. At KPIT, integrity is at the core of everything KPIT does, and remains steadfast in commitment to ethical business practices. All the policies including code of conduct can be found here https://www.kpit.com/investors/policies-reports-filings/.", "pb_11_textarea": "", "pb_12_textarea": "", "pb_13_textarea": "", "pb_14_textarea": "", "pb_15_textarea": "https://www.kpit.com/investors/policies-reports-filings/", "pb_16_textarea": "", "pb_17_textarea": "", "pb_18_textarea": "", "pb_19_textarea": "Yes, KPIT has implemented a comprehensive Occupational Health and Safety (OHS) Management System in most of the offices in India to ensure employee well-being. The OHS Management System incorporates various elements, including:\\n-Clear recommendations for safe work practices are included in KPIT’s policies and procedures.\\n-The ability to detect and reduce hazards at work proactively is made possible by Hazard Identification and Risk Assessment (HIRA).\\n-Employee training equips employees with the right skills and relevant expertise in their jobs proactively.\\n-Safety measures are implemented to maintain a secure work environment.\\n-Providing appropriate personal protective equipment to protect workers.\\n-Medical Fitness Assessments support the tracking of workers’ health via physical examinations.\\n-Being ready for emergencies enables the Company to handle potential incident-prone circumstances with efficiency.\\n-KPIT implemented Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) on safety-related issues and informed the staff\\nthrough various sources.\\n-Complied with all applicable health and safety rules as required by law.\\n-The Permitting System ensured that safety procedures are followed for specific tasks.\\n-Continuous review and improvement of the OHS Management System for enhanced employee well-being\\n\\nKPIT is dedicated to ensuring employee safety and well-being through a comprehensive Environmental, Occupational Health and Safety (EOHS) policy and has implemented (OHS) management system across all its offices. HIRA is a process that the Company utilizes to systematically identify hazards at work, evaluate risks, prioritize them, implement control measures, maintain vigilant tabs on their efficacy, document conclusions and communicate to the workforce to prevent workplace accidents.\\n\\nYes\\n\\nYes", "pb_20_textarea": "", "pb_21_textarea": "", "pb_22_textarea": "", "pb_23_textarea": "", "pb_24_textarea": "", "pb_25_textarea": "", "pb_26_textarea": "Yes", "pb_27_textarea": "", "pb_28_textarea": "", "pb_29_textarea": "false", "pb_30_textarea": "false", "pb_31_textarea": "", "pb_32_textarea": "", "pb_33_textarea": "", "pb_34_textarea": "", "pb_35_textarea": "Yes, KPIT has a Data privacy policy and the Company stands at the forefront of safeguarding the technological landscape with a comprehensive suite of security measures. The Company’s commitment to confidentiality, integrity, and availability of systems and data is unwavering. KPIT has fortified its defenses against evolving risks, including the expansion of device surfaces, by securing robust cyber insurance coverage. KPIT’s global cyber security framework is precisely crafted, spanning governance, policies, training, and incident management. KPIT’s approach includes proactive measures such as privacy impact assessments, data mapping, and third-party oversight to ensure compliance across geographies. To ensure the highest standards of information security, the Company maintains certifications in accordance with leading international standards such as Information Security Management (ISO/IEC 27001) and TISAX. TISAX is an European automotive industry-standard information security assessment catalog, focusing on key aspects of information security such as data protection and connections to third parties. Also, KPIT adheres to various statutory and regulatory compliance standards to safeguard the confidentiality, integrity, and availability of data provided to each client. KPIT is committed to upholding the trust and confidence of the clients by maintaining the highest levels of security and compliance across the operations.", "pb_07_option_radio": "Internal Policy", "pb_08_option_radio": "ESG/Sustainability function part of other board committee", "pb_10_option_radio": "Internal Policy", "pb_13_percentage_1": "", "pb_13_percentage_2": "", "pb_15_option_radio": "Internal Policy", "pb_19_option_radio": "Company has OHS management system, process to identify & process to report risks", "pb_26_option_radio": "Yes, it does", "pb_35_option_radio": "Internal Policy", "pb_06_option1_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_06_option2_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_12_option_number": "100.0", "pb_33_option_number": "0.0", "pb_02_option_number1": "0", "pb_02_option_number2": "0", "pb_03_option_number1": "9.1", "pb_03_option_number2": "66.67", "pb_28_option_checkbox": "", "pb_29_option_checkbox": "", "pb_30_option_checkbox": "", "pb_31_option_checkbox": "", "pb_05_option_checkbox1": "Employees", "pb_05_option_checkbox2": "Workers", "pb_05_option_checkbox3": "", "pb_05_option_checkbox4": "Value chain partners", "pb_05_option_checkbox5": "Customers", "pb_13_option_checkbox2": "", "pb_24_option1_checkbox": "", "pb_06_option1_checkbox1": "Code of conduct for Board of Directors/KMPs", "pb_06_option2_checkbox2": "Code of conduct for employees", "pb_14_option1_checkbox1": "", "pb_20_option1_checkbox1": "Lost Time Injury Frequency Rate", "pb_20_option1_checkbox2": "Fatalities", "pb_01_table_row1_num