77	84	\N	Capital Goods	{"pb_01": "information_available", "pb_02": "information_available", "pb_03": "information_available", "pb_04": "information_available", "pb_05": "information_available", "pb_06": "Information Available", "pb_07": "Information available", "pb_08": "information_available", "pb_09": "Information available", "pb_10": "information_available", "pb_11": "information_available", "pb_12": "information_available", "pb_13": "LCA conducted", "pb_14": "information_available", "pb_15": "information_available", "pb_16": "information_available", "pb_17": "information_available", "pb_18": "information_available", "pb_19": "information_available", "pb_20": "information_available", "pb_21": "information_available", "pb_22": "information_available", "pb_23": "information_available", "pb_24": "information_available", "pb_25": "information_available", "pb_26": "information_available", "pb_27": "information_available", "pb_28": "information_available", "pb_29": "information_available", "pb_30": "information_available", "pb_31": "information_available", "pb_32": "information_available", "pb_33": "No clear information", "pb_34": "information_available", "pb_35": "information_available", "pb_01_textarea": "", "pb_02_textarea": "", "pb_03_textarea": "", "pb_04_textarea": "", "pb_05_textarea": "", "pb_06_textarea": "", "pb_07_textarea": "", "pb_08_textarea": "CG has a Risk Management Committee which is currently responsible for reviewing Enterprise Risks including  Sustainability related issues. Recommendations of the Risk Management Committee are considered by the Board of Directors, as needed.\\n\\nAlong with this, CG also has a Corporate Social Responsibility (“CSR”) Committee in line with the provisions of Section 135 of the Act. The CSR Committee recommends, and the Board approves, the CSR expenditure budget and project plan. CSR projects of the Company are approved by the Board based on the recommendation of the CSR Committee. The Committee reviews CSR expenditure, activities undertaken and milestones achieved.", "pb_09_textarea": "", "pb_10_textarea": "Yes, CG has zero tolerance towards bribery and corruption and is committed to abiding by all laws and regulations. The Company has a code of conduct in place which covers all the aspects of anti-corruption or \\nanti-bribery policy.\\n\\nThe web link for Code of Conduct is given below:\\nhttps://www.cgglobal.com/policy\\nhttps://www.cgglobal.com/assets/pdf_files/CG_Code_of_Conduct_&_Business_Practices.pdf\\n\\nThe Policy reflects the commitment of the Company and its management for maintaining highest ethical standards while undertaking open and fair business practices and culture.", "pb_11_textarea": "", "pb_12_textarea": "", "pb_13_textarea": "", "pb_14_textarea": "", "pb_15_textarea": "Yes, the Company has human resource policy and diversity inclusion policy in place. CG is committed to create people-centric culture by providing equal opportunity in all the aspects of association and employment regardless of gender, ethnic background, disabilities, age, pregnancy, religion or other beliefs, sexual orientation or any other status as protected by law.\\n\\nThe Company has “Human Resource Policy “and “Human Rights Policy” with a clause on equal opportunity for people with disabilities. For policy, please refer https://www.cgglobal.com/policy.", "pb_16_textarea": "", "pb_17_textarea": "", "pb_18_textarea": "", "pb_19_textarea": "All of the Company’s manufacturing facilities are certified with ISO 45001:2018 - Occupational Health & Safety Management System Standard covering the site operations. Occupational Health Centre (OHC) is present at each of the plant locations as per the requirements of the Factories Act and Health and Safety Officer is also designated at each plant location. The Company has Health and Safety Committee across all its facilities consisting of workmen and employees. The Committee conducts monthly meetings to provide regular updates on health and safety aspects.\\n\\nIt also has Event Reporting System (ERS) which is accessible to workmen and employees for health-related hazards and upon receiving the complaint, corrective actions are taken to provide a solution and conclude the complaints in a timely manner. Half-yearly medical checkups are conducted for workmen who work in hazardous intensive processes and annual medical checkup is conducted for the entire workforce to ensure the safety of its people.\\n\\nSafety audits, cross-functional audits and internal audits are conducted as scheduled. Each of the entity’s manufacturing facilities is equipped with the required quantity of fire extinguishers, fire hydrant network, smoke detection and gas detection system. Emergency Preparedness and Response Plan is also available for all its plants on which basis each plant conducts mock drills to ensure its effectiveness and employee participation.\\n\\nOnline portal is used for reporting, analysing and assigning the corrective actions against identified hazards. CG has implemented Hazard Identification and Risk Assessment (HIRA) as a part of ISO 45001:2018 and regularly revisits the documents to make it dynamic. CG inspects the workplace for safety and health hazard and information is recorded in the Event Reporting System (ERS). CG has a work-permit system implemented across all factory locations to take care of routine and non-routine activities in a safe manner. In addition, Machine Risk Assessment (MRA) and Job Safety Analysis (JSA) are being performed for new machineries and/or activities.\\n\\nYes\\n\\nYes", "pb_20_textarea": "", "pb_21_textarea": "", "pb_22_textarea": "", "pb_23_textarea": "", "pb_24_textarea": "", "pb_25_textarea": "", "pb_26_textarea": "Yes", "pb_27_textarea": "", "pb_28_textarea": "the data reported is in Gj/per crore rupee of turnover. Cross checked calculation using revenue data.", "pb_29_textarea": "the data reported is in Kl/per crore rupee of turnover. Cross checked calculation using revenue data.", "pb_30_textarea": "false", "pb_31_textarea": "false", "pb_32_textarea": "", "pb_33_textarea": "", "pb_34_textarea": "", "pb_35_textarea": "Available on the Company's intranet", "pb_07_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_08_option_radio": "ESG/Sustainability function part of other board committee", "pb_10_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_13_percentage_1": "", "pb_13_percentage_2": "2", "pb_15_option_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_19_option_radio": "Company has OHS management system, process to identify & process to report risks", "pb_26_option_radio": "Yes, it does", "pb_35_option_radio": "Internal Policy", "pb_06_option1_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_06_option2_radio": "Publicly available Policy", "pb_12_option_number": "0.0", "pb_33_option_number": "3.24", "pb_02_option_number1": "2", "pb_02_option_number2": "2", "pb_03_option_number1": "25.0", "pb_03_option_number2": "0.0", "pb_28_option_checkbox": "", "pb_29_option_checkbox": "", "pb_30_option_checkbox": "", "pb_31_option_checkbox": "", "pb_05_option_checkbox1": "Employees", "pb_05_option_checkbox2": "Workers", "pb_05_option_checkbox3": "", "pb_05_option_checkbox4": "Value chain partners", "pb_05_option_checkbox5": "Customers", "pb_13_option_checkbox2": "", "pb_24_option1_checkbox": "", "pb_06_option1_checkbox1": "Code of conduct for Board of Directors/KMPs", "pb_06_option2_checkbox2": "Code of conduct for employees", "pb_14_option1_checkbox1": "", "pb_20_option1_checkbox1": "Lost Time Injury Frequency Rate", "pb_20_option1_checkbox2": "Fatalities", "pb_01_table_row1_number1": "93.38", "pb_01_table_row1_number2": "6.63", "pb_01_table_row1_number3": "98.39", "pb_01_table_row1_number4": "1.62", "pb_01_table_row2_number1": "83.04", "pb_01_table_row2_number2": "16.97", "pb_01_table_row2_number3": "95.97", "pb_01_table_row2_number4": "4.04", "pb_01_table_row3_number1": "91.4", "pb_01_table_row3_number2": "8.61", "pb_01_table_row3_number3": "96.64", "pb_01_table_row