223	270	\N	Financial Services	{"pb_01": "information_available", "pb_02": "information_available", "pb_03": "information_available", "pb_04": "information_available", "pb_05": "information_available", "pb_06": "Information Available", "pb_07": "Information available", "pb_08": "information_available", "pb_09": "Information available", "pb_10": "information_available", "pb_11": "information_available", "pb_12": "Indicator is not relevant for the industry", "pb_13": "No information", "pb_14": "information_available", "pb_15": "information_available", "pb_16": "information_available", "pb_17": "information_available", "pb_18": "information_available", "pb_19": "information_available", "pb_20": "information_available", "pb_21": "information_available", "pb_22": "information_available", "pb_23": "information_available", "pb_24": "information_available", "pb_25": "information_available", "pb_26": "information_available", "pb_27": "information_available", "pb_28": "No information", "pb_29": "No information", "pb_30": "No information", "pb_31": "No information", "pb_32": "No information", "pb_33": "No clear information", "pb_34": "No information", "pb_35": "information_available", "pb_01_textarea": "", "pb_02_textarea": "", "pb_03_textarea": "", "pb_04_textarea": "", "pb_05_textarea": "https://bandhanbank.com/sites/default/files/2022-09/Policy-on-Vigilance-and-Whistle-Blower-Mechanism.pdf", "pb_06_textarea": "https://bandhanbank.com/sites/default/files/2020-12/Code-Conduct-for-Directors.pdf", "pb_07_textarea": "", "pb_08_textarea": "The Corporate Social Responsibility & Sustainability Committee of the Board (‘CSR&SCB’) is responsible for the oversight of sustainability-related matters. The Committee is Chaired by a non-executive independent director and meets at least once in every quarter.", "pb_09_textarea": "", "pb_10_textarea": "", "pb_11_textarea": "", "pb_12_textarea": "", "pb_13_textarea": "", "pb_14_textarea": "", "pb_15_textarea": "Yes, the Bank has an equal opportunity statement in its HR policy and the extract of the same is also available in the Compendium of BRSR policies under Principle 5.\\n\\t\\nWeb-link: https://bandhanbank.com/sites/default/files/2023-01/Business-Responsibility-and-Sustainability-Reporting-policy-210123.pdf \\n\\nThe Bank believes that promoting equal opportunity in the workplace based on merit and ability can create an environment conducive to higher engagement and productivity. The Bank has achieved this by communicating the coverage of the policy to all employees in an appropriate and meaningful manner. In line with the sustainable development ethos of non-discrimination, and inclusive growth, the hiring and performance evaluation, compensation, training and employee benefits, are devoid of any discrimination based on caste, religion, disability, gender, sexual orientation, race, colour, ancestry, marital status or affiliation with a political, religious or union organization or majority/minority group.", "pb_16_textarea": "", "pb_17_textarea": "", "pb_18_textarea": "", "pb_19_textarea": "The Bank is cognizant of the responsibility towards providing a healthy and safe work environment to the employees and has developed a dedicated policy as part of the commitment to BRSR Principle 3. The Bank is in the process of evaluating the scope of the occupational health and safety management system to outline safety standards for the employees and customers to ensure regulatory compliance and promotion of public health and safety.  The Bank organizes regular training, such as mock drills on its premises for its employees on matters of fire safety, emergency response, and basic first aid.\\n\\nThe Bank in collaboration with the building management team of the office premises organizes and participates in mock fire drill sessions to create awareness amongst employees on how to evacuate in the event of fire or any other unforeseen contingency. Fire Marshalls and Fire Warden are nominated and trained to ensure 